						<summary>

						<p>Slab setup against the wall inside the Jaina temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">12th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This Chalukya record is plastered with cement. Hence nothing can be made out of it. There is a reference to a <hi rend="italic">shaṭ-karma-nirata</hi> ascetic [probably Bāḷachaṁdra] and to a ruler described as <hi rend="italic">Kalyaṇa-pura-varādīśvara,</hi> lord of the city of Kalyāṇa. The record seems to have registered some kind of grants probably to the ascetic made by the king or his feudatory officer. A few letters on the right side of the slab free from cement plaster, which can be made out, are noticed here.</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 12th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
